bodyHtml: |
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-12"><div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 card-shadow"><h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Why this tool matters in 2026</h2><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">Estimate your 2026 federal tax bill and effective tax rate using filing status and taxable income. This tax bracket calculator is helpful when evaluating raises, bonuses, side income, and yearly tax planning decisions. Good planning works best when you connect this page with the rest of your workflow on Finance Tools Hub.</p></div></section>
    
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-4"><div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 card-shadow"><h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">What this calculator does</h2><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">This page estimates federal income tax from taxable income rather than gross salary. That makes it useful for planning how much of a raise, bonus, or side-income stream may remain after federal taxes are applied.</p><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">It also helps users distinguish between a marginal tax bracket and an effective tax rate, which are often confused in day-to-day planning.</p></div></section>
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-4"><div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 card-shadow"><h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">How to interpret the result</h2><div class="mt-5 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4"><div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5"><h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Tax owed</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">This is the estimated federal income tax on the taxable income entered, based on the filing status selected.</p></div><div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5"><h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Effective tax rate</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">This shows the average federal tax rate across your taxable income, which is usually lower than the top bracket applied to the last dollars earned.</p></div></div></div></section>
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-4"><div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 card-shadow"><h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Common scenarios</h2><div class="mt-5 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4"><div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5"><h3 class="font-semibold">The raise analysis</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">How much of a salary increase might remain after federal tax instead of only increasing gross pay?</p></div><div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5"><h3 class="font-semibold">The bonus estimate</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">What does a large bonus or one-time income increase do to my annual federal tax picture?</p></div><div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-5"><h3 class="font-semibold">The side-income planner</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">How much extra federal tax could I face if I add freelance, consulting, or other taxable side income?</p></div></div></div></section>
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-4"><div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 card-shadow"><h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Sources and methodology</h2><p class="mt-4 text-slate-600">This calculator is an educational federal tax estimate. Actual tax liability can differ based on deductions, credits, withholding, and special tax treatment.</p><ul class="mt-4 list-disc pl-6 text-slate-600 space-y-2"><li>The calculator focuses on federal bracket logic, not a complete tax return.</li><li>State tax, credits, and special cases are not fully represented here.</li><li>Use the <a class="text-emerald-700 font-medium" href="/methodology.html">Methodology page</a> to review how Finance Tools Hub approaches assumptions and updates.</li></ul><div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3"><a href="/methodology.html" class="px-4 py-3 rounded-full bg-slate-900 text-white font-medium">Read methodology</a><a href="/about.html" class="px-4 py-3 rounded-full border border-slate-300 text-slate-800 font-medium">About the site</a><a href="/author-renato-bryant.html" class="px-4 py-3 rounded-full border border-slate-300 text-slate-800 font-medium">Author profile</a></div></div></section>

